{"title_hebrew":"אם אשכחך ירושלים","title_english":"Im Eshkachech Yerushalayim","artist":"Yaakov Shwekey","overview":"Based on Psalm 137, this is the eternal vow of the Jewish people never to forget Jerusalem. It is sung at weddings and times of remembrance, pledging that Jerusalem remains the 'head of our joy'.","youtube_url":"https://youtu.be/B8aal-gveRY?si=zdjQRpGMz-XnWeMk","lyrics":[{"hebrew":"אם לא אעלה","transliteration":"Im lo a'ale","english":"If I do not raise"},{"hebrew":"ואם לא אעלה","transliteration":"Ve'im lo a'ale","english":"And if I do not raise"},{"hebrew":"את ירושלים","transliteration":"Et Yerushalayim","english":"Jerusalem"},{"hebrew":"על ראש שמחתי","transliteration":"Al rosh simchati","english":"Above my highest joy"},{"hebrew":"על ראש על ראש שמחתי","transliteration":"Al rosh al rosh simchati","english":"Above, above my highest joy"},{"hebrew":"אם אשכחך ירושלים","transliteration":"Im eshkachech Yerushalayim","english":"If I forget you, O Jerusalem"},{"hebrew":"תשכח ימיני","transliteration":"Tishkach yemini","english":"Let my right hand forget (its skill)"},{"hebrew":"תדבק לשוני לחיכי","transliteration":"Tidbak leshoni lechiki","english":"Let my tongue stick to the roof of my mouth"},{"hebrew":"אם לא אזכרכי","transliteration":"Im lo ezkerechi","english":"If I do not remember you"},{"hebrew":"אם אשכח ירושלים","transliteration":"Im eshkach Yerushalayim","english":"If I forget Jerusalem"},{"hebrew":"תשכח ימיני","transliteration":"Tishkach yemini","english":"Let my right hand forget"},{"hebrew":"תדבק לשוני לחיכי","transliteration":"Tidbak leshoni lechiki","english":"Let my tongue stick to the roof of my mouth"},{"hebrew":"אם לא אזכרכי","transliteration":"Im lo ezkerechi","english":"If I do not remember you"}]}